main event: During the late evening and early morning hours of June 1, 1964, a luminous object floated in the sky over Willingboro, New Jersey.
interesting points: The sighting was reported almost a year after the observation,The object appeared to the observer as being shaped like a 'time',The observation was made using 70-year-old binoculars,The Air Force concluded the sighting as 'unidentifiable' and raised the possibility of psychological factors at play, The report includes a letter indicating that photographs from other sightings were analyzed but led to no positive identifications.
sighted object: luminous object shaped like a time
witness description: An individual who seems to be psychologically affected by the sighting
